title: rustdoc ICE: 'no entry found for key' with static referencing external type

labels.name: T-rustdoc
labels.description: Relevant to the rustdoc team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-nightly
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to nightly.

body:
### Code (Using `once-cell 1.9.0` + `rtsp-types 0.0.3`) ```Rust use once_cell::sync::Lazy; pub static X_ACCEPT_DYNAMIC_RATE: Lazy = Lazy::new(|| unimplemented!()); ``` (Minimized from ) ### Meta `rustdoc --version --verbose`: ``` rustdoc 1.60.0-nightly (88fb06a1f 2022-02-05) binary: rustdoc commit-hash: 88fb06a1f331926bccb448acdb52966fd1ec8a92 commit-date: 2022-02-05 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.60.0-nightly LLVM version: 13.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'no entry found for key', src/librustdoc/passes/collect_intra_doc_links.rs:930:16 ```
